    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If you need a stricter way to identify a "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "numerical"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " scalar, use\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "isinstance(x, numbers.Number)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", as that returns "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "False"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " for most\nnon-numerical elements such as strings."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In most cases "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.ndim(x) == 0.html",
              "href": "",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "ndim(x) == 0",
              "text": "we.ndim(x) == 0"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " should be used instead of this function,\nas that will also return true for 0d arrays. This is how numpy overloads\nfunctions in the style of the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "dx"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " arguments to "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/gradient",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "gradient",
              "text": "gradient"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and\nthe "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "bins"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " argument to "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/histogram",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "histogram",
              "text": "histogram"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". Some key differences:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "table",
          "raw_text": "\n\n\n\n\n\nx\n\nisscalar(x)\n\nwe.ndim(x) == 0\n\nPEP 3141 numeric objects\n(including builtins)\n\nTrue\n\nTrue\n\nbuiltin string and buffer objects\n\nTrue\n\nTrue\n\nother builtin objects, like\npathlib.Path, Exception,\nthe result of re.compile\n\nFalse\n\nTrue\n\nthird-party objects like\nmatplotlib.figure.Figure\n\nFalse\n\nTrue\n\nzero-dimensional numpy arrays\n\nFalse\n\nTrue\n\nother numpy arrays\n\nFalse\n\nFalse\n\nlist, tuple, and other\nsequence objects\n\nFalse\n\nFalse",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import whest as we"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar(3.1)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar(we.array(3.1))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "False"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar([3.1])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "False"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar(False)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar('numpy')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "NumPy supports PEP 3141 numbers:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "from fractions import Fraction"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar(Fraction(5, 17))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "from numbers import Number"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "we.isscalar(Number())"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
